kground-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><pre style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">autoRefresh :: View format monad result -&gt; View format monad result</pre><br style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Tahoma, Helvetica, FreeSans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Tahoma, Helvetica, FreeSans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">autoRefresh capture the form submissions and the links of the enclosed widget and send them via AJAX. The response is the new presentation of the widget, that is updated. No navigation occur. So a widget with autoRefresh can be used in heavyweight pages. If AJAX or javascript is not available, the widget is refreshed normally, via a new page.<br><br>Concerning the third widget &nbsp;(</span><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font face=\"courier new\">formWidget </font></span><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Tahoma, Helvetica, FreeSans, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">in the source code below) <a href=\"http://haskell-web.blogspot.com.es/2013/06/the-promising-land-of-monadic-formlets.html\" title=\"\" target=\"\">this article </a>explain how it works.</span><br>" 